name: Sebastian MILARDO v. The COASTAL RESOURCES MANAGEMENT COUNCIL et al.
name_abbreviation: Milardo v. Coastal Resources Management Council

parties: Sebastian MILARDO v. The COASTAL RESOURCES MANAGEMENT COUNCIL et al.

opinions.text:
ORDER
This case is assigned to the May, 1980 show cause calendar. The plaintiff is directed to appear and show cause why this appeal should not be dismissed since review of the Superior Court decision in this case should have been sought by petition for certiorari.

attorneys: Hogan & Hogan, Thomas S. Hogan, Donald J. Packer, Providence, for plaintiff.
Goldman, Biafore & Hines, Dennis H. Es-posito, Providence, for Coastal Resources Management Council of Rhode Island.
R. Daniel Prentiss, Chief Legal Counsel, Department of Environmental Management, Providence, for defendants.
casebody.head_matter:
Sebastian MILARDO v. The COASTAL RESOURCES MANAGEMENT COUNCIL et al.
No. 79-245-A.
Supreme Court of Rhode Island.
March 20, 1980.
Hogan & Hogan, Thomas S. Hogan, Donald J. Packer, Providence, for plaintiff.
Goldman, Biafore & Hines, Dennis H. Es-posito, Providence, for Coastal Resources Management Council of Rhode Island.
R. Daniel Prentiss, Chief Legal Counsel, Department of Environmental Management, Providence, for defendants.
